      "title": "Look What I Almost Stepped In...",
      "score": 0.04221147912915438,
      "text": "Look What I Almost Stepped In...\nLook What I Almost Stepped In... is the eighth studio album by the southern California punk rock band The Vandals, released in 2000 by Nitro Records. It was the band's final album for Nitro, as they moved to their own label Kung Fu Records the following year. Between June and August 2001, the group performed on the Warped Tour. Much of the album is characterized by the pop-punk music and humorous lyrics for which the band is known.",
