    {
      "node_id": "chunk:religion_in_ancient_rome_0",
      "passage_index": 4,
      "title": "Religion in ancient Rome",
      "score": 0.04155250118356255,
      "text": "Religion in ancient Rome\nLivy presents these as signs of widespread failure in Roman religio. The major prodigies included the spontaneous combustion of weapons, the apparent shrinking of the sun's disc, two moons in a daylit sky, a cosmic battle between sun and moon, a rain of red-hot stones, a bloody sweat on statues, and blood in fountains and on ears of corn: all were expiated by sacrifice of \"greater victims\". The minor prodigies were less warlike but equally unnatural; sheep become goats, a hen become a cock (and vice versa) – these were expiated with \"lesser victims\". The discovery of an androgynous four-year-old child was expiated by its drowning and the holy procession of 27 virgins to the temple of Juno Regina, singing a hymn to avert disaster: a lightning strike during the hymn rehearsals required further expiation. Religious restitution is proved only by Rome's victory.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.050123840473568215,
        "graph": 0.046614629743666765,
        "fact": 0.0
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:this_child_0",
      "passage_index": 16,
      "title": "This Child",
      "score": 0.04153846893446862,
      "text": "This Child\nThis Child is the second album by Susan Aglukark, released in 1995. The album was Susan's commercial breakthrough in Canada, spawning chart hits with \"O Siem\" and \"Hina Na Ho (Celebration)\", and making Susan the first Inuk performer ever to have a Top 40 hit.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05011108188643108,
        "graph": 0.04659124632310509,
        "fact": 0.0
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:the_official_story_0",
      "passage_index": 5,
      "title": "The Official Story",
      "score": 0.04153119085273596,
      "text": "The Official Story\nThe film deals with the story of an upper middle class couple who lives in Buenos Aires with an illegally adopted child. The mother comes to realize that her daughter may be the child of a desaparecido, a victim of the forced disappearances that occurred during Argentina's last military dictatorship (1976 - 1983), which was marred by widespread human rights violations and a genocide.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05007905298767317,
